post_text:
Friendly Reminder!

Commencement Exercises for the East Marion High School and West Marion High Class of 2020

Seniors who’ve met all the requirements set forth by the State Board of Education and MCSD Board of Trustees will graduate and walk across the stage to receive their diplomas. However, it’ll be a little different than in years past. The coronavirus pandemic has affected us as a society in more ways than most could have ever imagined. We are truly sorry that it has so drastically affected the end of the senior year of high school for the Class of 2020. This is a truly special time for all who’ve experienced it.

The class of 2020 and their parents have received specific details for our graduation ceremonies. We certainly regret that the entire MCSD family and community will be unable to attend our commencement exercises. Please make plans to watch it via Facebook Live on each school's Facebook page. Congratulations Class of 2020!

post_text: Marion County School District has been working diligently to create a plan to safely reopen our school district. The Mississippi Department of Education has provided all public school districts with considerations for reopening their schools. We are providing a survey for parents and grandparents to participate in regarding our students' return to school this fall. This survey will take less than 5 minutes to complete. This survey is for parents and grandparents who will have students enrolled in the Marion County School District during the 2020-2021 school year. Use this link https://forms.gle/zyXfookQZNMKjy9J6 to complete the survey. Thank you! We value your thoughts about the return-to-school!

post_text: The Marion County School District will provide summer enrichment learning through instructional packets for June 8 - July 16. Additionally, i-Ready online enrichment along with other programs are available for student use through July 17. Participation is not required but resources will be available to any student and/or parent that wants additional practice for their children. For grades K-8, the packets will focus on selected Language Arts and Math standards. For grades 9-12, the packets will focus on ACT Prep. The packets will be distributed on June 8, 2020. Follow the Grab N' Go lunch line route for WME, WMHS, EME and EMHS. WMP follow the bus line route. These resources will also be available online Monday, June 8, 2020 at MCSD webpage. Students who choose to participate may return the packets on July 16, 2020. Again, participation is not required, but is available to all MCSD students in grades K-12 who want some extra resources to help keep their skills sharp.

post_text: Happy Teacher Appreciation Week!
shared_text:
Wendy Rowley Bracey
May 6 at 8:18 AM ·

Happy Wednesday of Teacher Appreciation Week!

WE ARE FAMILY! Here is our golden rule: Have Faith in the Things You Do and You Won't Go Wrong! Thank you, teachers and staff, of MCSD for having faith in our students. You hard work has always paid off. Your MCSD school board and I were honored to receive the Lantern Award from the Mississippi School Board Association in February of 2020 for you earning a B accountability rating. Thank you for teaching and loving our students. That B stands for beautiful and blessed!

WE ARE MARION COUNTY!
WE INSPIRE EXCELLENCE!
WD>WS Well DONE is greater than well said!

WE LOVE YOU MARION COUNTY SCHOOL DISTRICT TEACHERS AND STAFF!

I do not own the rights to this music. I bought it right off iTunes, and I assure you that we know how to dance to it in MCSD.

post_text:
Marion County School District would like to thank you for your patience and kindness as we have worked fearlessly through these unprecedented times. We are so proud of each senior in our district, and we are committed to providing a safe, social distancing celebration for the Class of 2020 on the original weekend of graduation, May 22 & 23, 2020. These evenings will be great and full of surprises for our seniors.

We will celebrate a traditional graduation ceremony on the weekend of June 26, 2020 with a backup plan of July 24, 2020. A detailed letter will be sent to parents about "The Celebration of the Class of 2020" and the traditional "Graduation Commencement."

We will follow CDC recommendations on public gatherings at all times related to our celebration and graduation.

post_text:
Marion County School District Family,

The Mississippi Department of Education has requested that we send out this survey to the parent(s)/guardian(s) of students in our district. The purpose of the survey is to get a better understanding of the status of internet connectivity and availability of devices to children in our district while they are at home. It may also be used to help address the availability of broadband internet service or the lack thereof in the future.

Please complete one survey per home. You may complete this form at the link below, on our district webpage at our Covid-19 link, or complete the paper form you will receive in the the grab-n-go lunch line. If you choose to complete the paper copy, you can return it through the grab-n-go lunch line. There will be someone designated to take up surveys as you exit the lunch line each day. We have set May 8th as our deadline.

Thank you for your help!

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSc57tQApBKdpt4TO7R86hWLNAtbKWLZ1Gu8NRtRIkfwUfiatQ/viewform

Good Morning Marion County School District Family,

Marion County School District will be closed from March 23, 2020 through April 17, 2020. Thank you for your patience as we awaited Governor Reeves announcement.

All letters and district resources concerning the COVID-19 can be found on our district website.

This is the link to our website. http://www.marionk12.org/covid19
Please check here for up-dates as information will continue to change.

My email is wbracey@marionk12.org. Feel free to email me with any questions or concerns. God Bless You!

Thank you,
Wendy Bracey

Good Morning Marion County School District Family,

Marion County School District will be closed from March 23, 2020 through April 17, 2020. Thank you for your patience as we awaited Governor Reeves announcement.

All letters and district resources concerning the COVID-19 can be found on our district website.

This is the link to our website. http://www.marionk12.org/covid19
Please check here for up-dates as information will continue to change.

My email is wbracey@marionk12.org. Feel free to email me with any questions or concerns. God Bless You!

Thank you,
Wendy Bracey

Good Evening Marion County School District,

I know you all are anxiously awaiting news about school closure. Governor Reeves will announce plans regarding potential school closure after a 10:00 a.m. meeting tomorrow. Our official document regarding school closure will be forthcoming on Thursday. I am grateful for such an awesome leadership team and school board who have worked diligently with administrators and parents to secure a very detailed next step action plan for student learning and our feeding program. God bless you. Have a wonderful evening! Enjoy the remainder of your Spring Break as well as you can. Please remember to pray for our country, state, county, and town.

Sincerely,
Wendy Bracey
Superintendent

post_text:
Good Morning Marion County School District,

As we continue to monitor the the Coronavirus (COVID-19) as we are on Spring Break; this includes staying in constant contact with the Mississippi State Department of Health and state offices in order to make the most informed decisions for the limiting of COVID-19.

We have just received this letter from the MHSAA. Please read the document carefully.

Effective immediately, March 16, all MHSAA interscholastic sports and fine-arts activities, competitions, and practices are suspended through March 29 and until further notice. This suspension applies whether or not a school is open or closed during this timeline.

Thank you,
Wendy

shared_text:
Wendy Rowley Bracey
March 6 at 11:53 PM ·

Today, PREPS held a superintendents breakfast. I had the honor of joining my fellow superintendents across the state of MS in meeting with education majors from William Carey University and Delta State University. I certainly enjoyed talking with them about sharing their future teaching careers with us in MCSD. I loved hearing that new teacher excitement in their voices and seeing the smiles on their faces as they shared their goals and plans for teaching. I also loved sharing with them why Marion County is a wonderful place to work. I appreciate Dr. Ben Burnett and Dr. Patti Permenter for this wonderful opportunity to meet with these future educators. I was super honored to be asked to pray the opening prayer at the breakfast! May all these future teachers love education like I have loved it throughout my time as an educator. Teaching is the best career choice ever.
#WEAREMARIONCOUNTY!
#WEINSPIREEXCELLENCE!

You can inspire others. Tell everyone—your friends and family, your neighbors and co-workers—that you will complete the census, and tell them why it’s important that they respond too.

Census results have an impact on planning and funding for health clinics and highways, fire departments and disaster response, education programs such as Head Start and college tuition assistance, and so much more.

post_text:
The Census matters! Please respond by completing your packet. It should be in your mailbox next week.

The number of people that participate has everything to do with the federal monies that the Marion County School District receives.

Education is just one vital service that could be negatively impacted if citizens don’t participate.

Keep in mind, Census numbers are relied on for 10 years.

If our population is not accurately reflected in the count, it could impact our students throughout their school career.

post_text: Good Evening! We have been in close contact with the Emergency Management Team and Marion County Sheriff's Team. Marion County School District will have school tomorrow. If you are in an area that does not permit travel, please do what is best for you and your child. In the event that your child can’t make it to school, we understand. Please send a parent note with your child when he/she returns to school for an excused absence. In the event that there would be a change through the night, you will be notified by 6:00 a.m. in the morning. Enjoy the remainder of your Sunday evening and stay safe.

post_text: National School Board Appreciation Week was February 10-14, 2020. MCSD celebrated their school board members at the board meeting held at WMHS on Thursday evening. Prior to the meeting, board members enjoyed a tour of the school by Mrs. Dunaway. She her team also provided a very nice evening of Valentine's refreshments and coffee for their guests. Mrs. Bracey, superintendent, presented their board awards and thanked them for their service to the MCSD. Then, the CTE students celebrated National Career and Technical Education month by honoring the Marion County School Board and Ms. Wendy Bracey with gifts their classes had made for school board appreciation night. It was a great evening. Thank you to all of our community members who attended.

Callie and I would like to encourage you to bundle up our Eagles and Trojans. The temperature has dropped significantly, and Mr. Patrick from WDAM has said the temperatures will continue to drop this morning. It is a very windy morning, so break out the coats, gloves, and toboggans. We will have a nice warm sausage biscuit ready for our darlings for breakfast and nice hot chicken sausage gumbo for lunch. Bus drivers are warming up the buses, and the classrooms will be nice and warm for a great day of learning. Stay warm and have a beautiful day.
Wendy Bracey
Superintendent

Administrative Procedures Act (APA) Notice
OFFICE OF ACCREDITATION

Chapter 36, Rule 36.4: Assessments Required For Graduation



On September 19, 2019, the State Board of Education (SBE) granted approval to begin the Administrative Procedures Act (APA) process to revise Miss. Admin. Code 7-3:36.4, State Board Policy Chapter 36, Rule 36.4: Assessments Required for Graduation.

The proposed revision would eliminate the administration of the U. S. History End-of-Course assessment effective school year 2020-2021.

Please submit written comments to Dr. Jo Ann Malone, Office of Accreditation, 359 N. West Street, Post Office Box 771, Jackson, MS 39205-0771. You may also submit comments in writing by e-mail (accreditation@mdek12.org).

All public comments must be received in the Office of Accreditation no later than 5:00 p.m. on October 22, 2019. APA Comments will be presented to the SBE on November 7, 2019.

post_text: We are excited to announce that Marion County School District is a B district according to the accountability results approved by the MDE state board of education today. Within the district, we have one “A” rated school, West Marion Primary, one “B” rated school, West Marion High School, and 3 “C” rated schools, West Marion Elementary, East Marion Elementary, and East Marion High School. The state board of education’s goal #6 is that every school and district will be a C or better. We are pleased that we have met that goal. We would like to thank our students, teachers, administrators, support staff, parents, and community members for your dedication, hard work, and support. We look forward to sharing more of the details of the data in the weeks to come.

shared_text:
Wendy Rowley Bracey is with Traci McMichael Sullivan and 2 others.
July 19, 2019 at 7:14 AM ·

2018-2019 Kindergarten Readiness Results were released by MDE yesterday, July 18, 2019.

Congratulations to West Marion Primary on being above the state average.

Thank you to East and West for working so hard. East students improved their scale from Fall to Spring by 208 points from 466 to 674. West Marion Primary increased their scale score from Fall to Spring by 263 points 460 to 723.

Thank you, Vicki Boone, Traci McMichael Sullivan, and Chase Robbins along with your awesome teachers, for working hard to ensure our children are well-educated. Thank you precious darling little students for your love for learning!

Always remember principals, parents, and staff, our students are always much more than a test score to me.

You can see the results at the following link:

https://www.mdek12.org/sites/default/files/Offices/MDE/OEA/OPR/2019/2019_kra_results_kg_fy2019_post-test_final.pdf
